The sooner I finish filming,
the sooner I can join you.

950
00:59:51,040 --> 00:59:53,270
Did you know your toupee was on
a little crooked?

951
00:59:53,320 --> 00:59:55,276
- What?
- Yeah.

952
00:59:55,320 --> 00:59:59,552
Are you kidding? How many times
have I told you to watch my hair?

953
00:59:59,600 --> 01:00:02,831
Great timing, Steve.
It'd be nice to have him home for a while.

954
01:00:02,880 --> 01:00:05,758
It's a wonder Dodd even knows
what he looks like.

955
01:00:08,200 --> 01:00:11,112
Great having them both at the same studio,
isn't it?

956
01:00:13,000 --> 01:00:16,788
# There are so many
fabulous faraway places to see

957
01:00:18,720 --> 01:00:23,077
<i># Such as Mexico, Sweden,
Hawaii, Japan and Capri</i>

958
01:00:25,040 --> 01:00:28,112
# There's so many exciting
and wonderful places

959
01:00:28,160 --> 01:00:31,596
<i># Mountains and jungles and desert oases</i>

960
01:00:31,640 --> 01:00:34,359
# Pleasant as home is, it isn't what Rome is

961
01:00:34,400 --> 01:00:36,675
# So why stay there?

962
01:00:36,720 --> 01:00:41,157
# When there are so many
fabulous faraway places to see

963
01:00:43,000 --> 01:00:45,878
<i># Why should Spain and Tahiti and Rio</i>

964
01:00:45,920 --> 01:00:49,196
# Just be only names to you and me

965
01:00:49,240 --> 01:00:52,676
# I feel certain there's people
we'd be glad to know there

966
01:00:52,720 --> 01:00:55,837
# So tell me why don't we
get up and just go there

967
01:00:55,880 --> 01:00:59,475
# Go to those fabulous places
where we long to be

968
01:01:01,960 --> 01:01:04,872
# Like Bangkok and Hong Kong
and Paris and Venice

969
01:01:04,920 --> 01:01:08,037
# Tokyo and Cairo and Lisbon and London

970
01:01:08,080 --> 01:01:11,231
<i># Siam, Siena, Vienna, Verona</i>

971
01:01:11,280 --> 01:01:14,078
<i># Java, Jamaica, Bombay, Barcelona</i>

972
01:01:14,120 --> 01:01:18,318
# Show me those fabulous places

973
01:01:18,360 --> 01:01:23,798
# We're longing to see

974
01:01:30,040 --> 01:01:32,031
(Cheering and applause)

975
01:01:43,720 --> 01:01:46,109
So this is your suite, Bobby and Mrs Darin.

976
01:01:47,640 --> 01:01:50,837
Bar, fire pit. The bathroom's over there.

977
01:01:50,880 --> 01:01:53,189
- And the living room's this way, sir.
- Thank you.

978
01:01:53,240 --> 01:01:55,674
- I'll just put your luggage in.
- Great, thank you.

979
01:01:55,720 --> 01:01:57,836
Look at this, baby.

980
01:01:57,880 --> 01:01:59,996
Gonna be a hot night in Vegas.

981
01:02:07,480 --> 01:02:10,711
- Anything else I can do for you?
- No, that's all. Thank you.

982
01:02:10,760 --> 01:02:14,116
- Would you like to have some ice?
- No, I'm great. There you go.

983
01:02:14,160 --> 01:02:16,116
- Where are you from?
- I'm from Germany.

984
01:02:16,160 --> 01:02:18,116
That's a terrific city. Thank you.

985
01:02:18,160 --> 01:02:21,550
- I'm a big fan, Mr Darin.
- That's very kind. Good night.

986
01:02:26,360 --> 01:02:28,316
<i>Sandush...</i>

987
01:02:28,360 --> 01:02:31,989
Don't you think you're drinking
a little bit too much lately?

988
01:02:32,040 --> 01:02:34,713
No, actually I don't think
I've had enough to drink.

989
01:02:34,760 --> 01:02:37,558
OK, what's the problem?

990
01:02:37,600 --> 01:02:39,716
I just want us to be together.

991
01:02:39,760 --> 01:02:43,230
<i>- We are together, baby, look.
- I mean some kind of normal schedule.</i>

992
01:02:43,280 --> 01:02:45,748
We have a baby,
and if I don't see you up on stage,

993
01:02:45,800 --> 01:02:48,758
- I don't see you at all.
- Well, you're here, too.

994
01:02:48,800 --> 01:02:52,031
Recording or performing or filming
or making appearances.

995
01:02:52,080 --> 01:02:55,959
- Why can't we just stay home?
- Honey, performing is my life.

996
01:02:57,000 --> 01:02:59,878
- Well, what about me?
- You're here, aren't you?

997
01:02:59,920 --> 01:03:02,957
- Yeah, with all of them.
- They're a part of my life.

998
01:03:03,000 --> 01:03:05,958
Just like Mary is a part of
your life and now a part of ours.

999
01:03:06,000 --> 01:03:08,673
They are our family. All of them, like it or not.

1000
01:03:08,720 --> 01:03:10,915
I can't just stop working to tour with you.

1001
01:03:10,960 --> 01:03:13,030
- Yes, you can.
- No, I can't.

1002
01:03:13,080 --> 01:03:15,230
- You can.
- No. I'm an actress.

1003
01:03:15,280 --> 01:03:17,236
Making movies is what I do.

1004
01:03:17,280 --> 01:03:19,510
Kissing Troy Donahue's not acting.

1005
01:03:19,560 --> 01:03:23,155
- Oh, yeah? Then you try it.
- I'd rather not.

1006
01:03:23,200 --> 01:03:25,714
Hey, what a face.

1007
01:03:41,920 --> 01:03:43,876
- You should lock the door.
- Why?

1008
01:03:43,920 --> 01:03:46,388
- Before someone comes in.
- Nobody's coming in.

1009
01:03:46,440 --> 01:03:48,908
Yesterday, Charlie walked in on me
taking a shower.

1010
01:03:48,960 --> 01:03:51,155
<i>You're kidding? What did he want?</i>

1011
01:03:51,200 --> 01:03:53,794
He asked me if I wanted
a corned beef sandwich.

1012
01:03:56,000 --> 01:03:59,197
- Do you?
- (Giggles) Ooh, honey.

1013
01:04:03,600 --> 01:04:06,353
It's OK. It's just us.

1014
01:04:07,920 --> 01:04:11,151
Bobby! Whoa, sorry.
But I was right about the war picture.

1015
01:04:11,200 --> 01:04:14,670
Get your speech ready cos after the tour,
you're going to the Oscars, pal.

1016
01:04:14,720 --> 01:04:19,555
- You just got nominated.
- Hallelujah! Yes! Yes!

1017
01:04:19,600 --> 01:04:21,033
Oh, Christ.

1018
01:04:22,080 --> 01:04:25,755
<i>And the nominees are,
Nick Adams in Twilight Of Honour.</i>

1019
01:04:26,880 --> 01:04:30,429
<i>Bobby Darin in Captain Newman, MD.</i>

1020
01:04:31,800 --> 01:04:33,791
<i>Melvyn Douglas in Hud.</i>

1021
01:04:35,200 --> 01:04:39,113
<i>- Hugh Griffith in Tom Jones.
- Hello!</i>

1022
01:04:39,160 --> 01:04:41,151
<i>And John Huston in The Cardinal.</i>

1023
01:04:42,320 --> 01:04:44,311
<i>And the winner is...</i>

1024
01:04:49,280 --> 01:04:51,475
<i>Melvyn Douglas? Melvyn Douglas?</i>

1025
01:04:51,520 --> 01:04:54,432
My blood is up there on the screen
and they give it to him!

1026
01:04:54,480 --> 01:04:56,869
Unzip me, please.

1027
01:04:56,920 --> 01:04:59,115
"You don't care about people, Hud.

1028
01:04:59,160 --> 01:05:01,310
You don't give a damn about 'em."

1029
01:05:07,840 --> 01:05:09,796
<i>I heard he was dying or something.</i>

1030
01:05:09,840 --> 01:05:12,513
- It's a sympathy vote.
- He's dying? I'm the one dying!

1031
01:05:12,560 --> 01:05:15,233
Way before he was dying, I was dying.
Where's my sympathy?

1032
01:05:15,280 --> 01:05:17,874
You're doing fine feeling sorry for yourself
all alone.

1033
01:05:17,920 --> 01:05:21,595
"Stick your finger up my ass, Alma,
and wiggle it, just like the doctor does."

1034
01:05:21,640 --> 01:05:24,950
It's an honour just to be nominated.
I've never been nominated.

1035
01:05:25,000 --> 01:05:27,833
All your Hollywood friends
probably voted against me.

1036
01:05:27,880 --> 01:05:30,678
- I voted for you, Bobby.
- It's BD. What time's the car?

1037
01:05:30,720 --> 01:05:32,995
All right, see you then.
All the slaps and smiles,

1038
01:05:33,040 --> 01:05:34,598
and I'm a goddamn joke out there.

1039
01:05:34,640 --> 01:05:36,710
Not as big of a joke as you are right now.

1040
01:05:36,760 --> 01:05:40,389
Warren Beatty is there with Leslie Caron,
nominated for Best Actress,

1041
01:05:40,440 --> 01:05:42,112
and I'm there with Gidget.

1042
01:05:42,160 --> 01:05:44,310
Leslie Caron is not box office!

1043
01:05:44,360 --> 01:05:47,591
- Those people don't care about that.
- It's all they give a shit about.

1044
01:05:47,640 --> 01:05:50,359
Only people from the Bronx
actually care about the Oscars.

1045
01:05:50,400 --> 01:05:53,836
Melvyn Douglas is married to a
congresswoman, I'm married to Tammy.

1046
01:05:53,880 --> 01:05:57,111
It took Melvyn Douglas 40 years
to get a Supporting Actor's face.

1047
01:05:57,160 --> 01:05:59,151
You should be happy you did it in just two.

1048
01:06:02,640 --> 01:06:05,598
You know what?
Maybe I'll just go back out on tour.

1049
01:06:05,640 --> 01:06:08,996
Oh, that's just great, Bobby.
That's just fucking great!

1050
01:06:09,040 --> 01:06:11,395
Like usual, you leave Dodd and me behind.

1051
01:06:11,440 --> 01:06:13,396
When you're on the boards, it's real.

1052
01:06:13,440 --> 01:06:15,670
The audience is right there, you can feel 'em.

1053
01:06:15,720 --> 01:06:19,998
- Maybe movie audiences are too sober for you.
- It's reality, the nightclubs are reality.

1054
01:06:20,040 --> 01:06:22,679
It's not like the frickin' movies that are all fake!

1055
01:06:22,720 --> 01:06:26,918
I just have one thing to say to you,
Mr Reality, Mr King of Reality -

1056
01:06:26,960 --> 01:06:28,996
your toupee's on crooked!

1057
01:06:29,040 --> 01:06:32,430
You're always trying to undermine me
every time I go on stage like that!

1058
01:06:32,480 --> 01:06:36,155
Telling me I've got a pimple on my nose.
I'm goddamn sick of it!

1059
01:06:36,200 --> 01:06:38,668
- What are you doing?
- What does it look like?

1060
01:06:38,720 --> 01:06:41,712
No, you don't. Oh, no, you don't!

1061
01:06:41,760 --> 01:06:45,355
You don't leave me! I leave you!

1062
01:06:45,400 --> 01:06:48,756
The cars and the clothes
and the hair and the premiere.

1063
01:06:48,800 --> 01:06:50,916
It's bullshit. I'm sick of all of it.

1064
01:06:50,960 --> 01:06:52,916
I'm telling you I'm out of here.

1065
01:06:52,960 --> 01:06:55,679
You stay here cos you gotta take care of Dodd.

1066
01:06:55,720 --> 01:06:57,756
The nanny's here. He's fine!

1067
01:06:59,160 --> 01:07:02,152
You had a chance to be happy
and you messed it up!

1068
01:07:02,200 --> 01:07:04,156
Well, you...

1069
01:07:04,200 --> 01:07:06,316
You come... You...

1070
01:07:07,360 --> 01:07:09,635
<i>You come back here!</i>

1071
01:07:10,680 --> 01:07:15,595
<i>SANDRA: You think it's gonna be easy
to find somebody who'll love you?</i>

1072
01:07:15,640 --> 01:07:21,590
A big-nosed, self-centred, mean, nasty,
balding, little shithead with a bad heart?

1073
01:07:22,840 --> 01:07:25,798
Well, you go for it, honey, cos I am through!

1074
01:07:25,840 --> 01:07:28,718
# Charade

1075
01:07:28,760 --> 01:07:31,320
# Fate seemed to pull the strings

1076
01:07:31,360 --> 01:07:34,511
# I turned and you were gone

1077
01:07:34,560 --> 01:07:38,030
# While from the darkened wings

1078
01:07:38,080 --> 01:07:41,959
# The music box played on and on

1079
01:07:42,000 --> 01:07:45,629
# Sad little serenade

1080
01:07:45,680 --> 01:07:48,353
# Song of my heart's composing

1081
01:07:49,360 --> 01:07:52,591
# I hear it still, I guess I always will

1082
01:07:52,640 --> 01:07:56,633
# Best on the bill

1083
01:07:56,680 --> 01:07:58,989
# Charade!

1084
01:08:23,280 --> 01:08:25,271
My baby.

1085
01:08:28,720 --> 01:08:30,870
Maybe you're right.

1086
01:08:30,920 --> 01:08:34,674
Maybe you're right about all
these people being around us all the time.

1087
01:08:34,720 --> 01:08:36,995
Maybe it should just be us.

1088
01:08:38,440 --> 01:08:42,069
# Whatever you've done, it's all over

1089
01:08:44,320 --> 01:08:48,108
# Wherever you've been is so strange

1090
01:08:50,760 --> 01:08:54,639
# Yesterday's long gone for ever
- Daddy, I found your hair!

1091
01:08:54,680 --> 01:08:56,750
That's good, Moose, cos I left it somewhere!

1092
01:08:56,800 --> 01:08:59,997
# Damned if what you're feeling isn't change...

1093
01:09:01,600 --> 01:09:03,875
<i>So I did stay home for a while.</i>

1094
01:09:03,920 --> 01:09:06,480
<i>The 1960s rushed by like a locomotive,</i>

1095
01:09:06,520 --> 01:09:08,954
<i>while Dodd grew up like a moose.</i>

1096
01:09:09,000 --> 01:09:11,798
<i>Sandy and I did a couple of movies together
but they were dogs.</i>

1097
01:09:11,840 --> 01:09:15,389
<i>The music scene was changing
as dramatically as the country.</i>

1098
01:09:15,440 --> 01:09:19,115
<i>Nightclubs were out
and big venues like stadiums were in.</i>

1099
01:09:19,160 --> 01:09:23,358
<i>I was suddenly irrelevant,
my stage literally disappearing.</i>

1100
01:09:23,400 --> 01:09:26,915
<i>I tried to write new music
and got involved in politics</i>

1101
01:09:26,960 --> 01:09:29,349
<i>because we were now a country at war.</i>

1102
01:09:30,480 --> 01:09:32,710
<i>But the fact was, I was a balding chart singer</i>

1103
01:09:32,760 --> 01:09:36,639
<i>who hadn't had a hit in years,
and who should be dead.</i>

1104
01:09:36,680 --> 01:09:38,636
<i>INTERVIEWER: So why Kennedy?</i>

1105
01:09:38,680 --> 01:09:41,956
Like most people in this country,
I'm fed up with all the insanity.

1106
01:09:42,000 --> 01:09:44,468
The assassination of our president,
Vietnam, riots.

1107
01:09:44,520 --> 01:09:47,193
<i>I'm looking for salvation from all the madness,</i>

1108
01:09:47,240 --> 01:09:49,879
and then along comes
another guy named Bobby.

1109
01:09:49,920 --> 01:09:54,072
<i>Now, here is a no-bullshit guy
who is committed, passionate,</i>

1110
01:09:54,120 --> 01:09:57,590
who really cares -
I've completely dedicated myself to this man.

1111
01:09:57,640 --> 01:09:59,870
<i>I think he may be this country's last hope.</i>

1112
01:10:00,720 --> 01:10:01,869
Go out and vote.

1113
01:10:01,920 --> 01:10:04,388
<i>While it seemed Bobby Kennedy
might heal the country,</i>

1114
01:10:04,440 --> 01:10:06,635
<i>Sandy and I drifted farther and farther apart.</i>

1115
01:10:07,720 --> 01:10:10,951
Bobby, why do you sing
the same songs every night?

1116
01:10:13,040 --> 01:10:14,758
Isn't it boring?

1117
01:10:14,800 --> 01:10:16,313
Well, honey, it's an act.

1118
01:10:16,360 --> 01:10:19,193
Do you expect me to sing
different songs every night?

1119
01:10:19,240 --> 01:10:21,276
Why not? I don't make the same movies.

1120
01:10:21,320 --> 01:10:24,437
Well, actually, you do. Sweet, little, innocent...

1121
01:10:24,480 --> 01:10:25,595
Excuse me!

1122
01:10:25,640 --> 01:10:29,633
But I think I know what people want
in the movies nowadays, OK?

1123
01:10:29,680 --> 01:10:32,399
<i>You may be the expert in... in music,</i>

1124
01:10:32,440 --> 01:10:37,355
<i>but I... I have had
years of movie experience!</i>

1125
01:10:37,400 --> 01:10:39,356
<i>Not bad, Sand.</i>

1126
01:10:39,400 --> 01:10:42,392
Would've been even better
without the slur in your voice.

1127
01:10:46,440 --> 01:10:47,998
<i>My sister came out to stay with us,</i>

1128
01:10:48,040 --> 01:10:51,635
<i>but her real reason for coming
I couldn't have possibly imagined.</i>

1129
01:10:51,680 --> 01:10:56,515
Listen, Bobby, there's a reason
I felt I had to come and stay with you.

1130
01:10:56,560 --> 01:10:58,516
Yeah, what?

1131
01:10:59,560 --> 01:11:03,235
I heard you were going into politics.
You still thinkin' about doing that?

1132
01:11:03,280 --> 01:11:06,192
Well, I'm considering it.
I mean, they've asked me.

1133
01:11:06,240 --> 01:11:08,800
You know how the papers try and smear people

1134
01:11:08,840 --> 01:11:12,276
with things from their past
when they're gonna run for office?

1135
01:11:12,320 --> 01:11:14,550
Mm-hm. Yeah. So what?

1136
01:11:14,600 --> 01:11:19,833
There's something about your past
that I think it's finally time for you to know.

1137
01:11:19,880 --> 01:11:21,871
What are you talking about?

1138
01:11:22,720 --> 01:11:24,392
It's about Polly.

1139
01:11:25,400 --> 01:11:27,960
She wasn't who you thought she was, Bobby.

1140
01:11:28,000 --> 01:11:30,468
She was the best mother
in the whole goddamn world.

1141
01:11:30,520 --> 01:11:33,239
She was, because she was
my mother, so I know it's true.

1142
01:11:33,280 --> 01:11:37,034
<i>- Then take that back!
- She was a wonderful person and mother.</i>

1143
01:11:37,080 --> 01:11:40,789
But what I think you really need now
is the truth.

1144
01:11:40,840 --> 01:11:42,876
The truth about your mother.

1145
01:11:44,400 --> 01:11:46,231
And the truth is...

1146
01:11:47,280 --> 01:11:50,317
Polly was not your mother.

1147
01:11:51,360 --> 01:11:53,351
Sam was not your father.

1148
01:11:55,760 --> 01:11:57,751
You ain't my brother, Bobby.

1149
01:12:03,200 --> 01:12:07,159
We swore we would never let you find out.

1150
01:12:11,680 --> 01:12:13,955
<i>Polly was my mother.</i>

1151
01:12:15,760 --> 01:12:17,751
<i>Not yours.</i>

1152
01:12:20,560 --> 01:12:23,472
<i>She was your grandmother.</i>

1153
01:12:25,680 --> 01:12:26,999
<i>Sweetheart...</i>

1154
01:12:28,440 --> 01:12:30,317
I'm not your sister.

1155
01:12:35,480 --> 01:12:37,630
Bobby, I'm your mother.

1156
01:12:40,680 --> 01:12:44,958
We made a pact that we would never tell you.

1157
01:12:45,800 --> 01:12:47,472
Is she kidding?

1158
01:12:47,520 --> 01:12:50,717
She got pregnant when she was 17.

1159
01:12:50,760 --> 01:12:54,799
It's true. I didn't want you to be a bastard,
so I gave you to mama,

1160
01:12:54,840 --> 01:12:56,876
so that way no-one could call you one.

1161
01:12:56,920 --> 01:12:58,751
She couldn't give you up for adoption.

1162
01:12:58,800 --> 01:13:02,429
When I went off to the hospital
when it was time for you to be born,

1163
01:13:02,480 --> 01:13:06,109
Mama moved us to the Bronx
where we didn't know nobody.

1164
01:13:06,160 --> 01:13:12,110
And then when I came back,
we said you were her baby, not mine.

1165
01:13:12,160 --> 01:13:14,116
But that way, I could keep you.

1166
01:13:14,160 --> 01:13:16,720
Do you realise what you're saying to me?

1167
01:13:16,760 --> 01:13:18,716
We did it to protect you, Bobby.

1168
01:13:18,760 --> 01:13:22,150
You need me now. I can really be here for you.

1169
01:13:22,200 --> 01:13:24,236
You're lost.

1170
01:13:24,280 --> 01:13:28,558
You can finally have the mother
that you never really had.

1171
01:13:30,840 --> 01:13:33,115
# THE ROLLING STONES: Let It Loose

1172
01:13:34,920 --> 01:13:37,992
# Who's that woman on your arm

1173
01:13:44,320 --> 01:13:47,232
# All dressed up to do you harm?

1174
01:13:50,520 --> 01:13:52,988
# And I'm hip to what...

1175
01:13:53,040 --> 01:13:55,793
Who was my father?

1176
01:13:55,840 --> 01:13:57,398
Oh, Bobby.

1177
01:13:58,440 --> 01:14:00,954
I was dating a lot of guys back then.

1178
01:14:01,000 --> 01:14:03,309
Who was my father?

1179
01:14:11,880 --> 01:14:15,031
# Bit off more than I can chew

1180
01:14:21,600 --> 01:14:25,195
# And I knew what it was leading to

1181
01:14:26,800 --> 01:14:30,236
# Some things, well, I can't refuse

1182
01:14:35,200 --> 01:14:40,752
# One of them, one of them the bedroom blues

1183
01:14:47,880 --> 01:14:52,670
# She delivers right on time

1184
01:14:56,440 --> 01:15:00,956
# I can't resist a corny line

1185
01:15:02,720 --> 01:15:08,716
# But take the shine right off your shoes

1186
01:15:10,520 --> 01:15:16,470
# Carrying, carrying the bedroom blues

1187
01:15:46,640 --> 01:15:48,437
(Waves break on shore)

1188
01:17:17,880 --> 01:17:19,871
(Strums chords)

1189
01:17:27,720 --> 01:17:32,077
# Come and sing a simple song of freedom

1190
01:17:34,800 --> 01:17:38,395
# Sing it like you've never sung before

1191
01:17:40,640 --> 01:17:42,949
# Let it fill the air

1192
01:17:43,000 --> 01:17:47,152
# Tell the people everywhere

1193
01:17:48,440 --> 01:17:52,433
# We the people here don't want a war

1194
01:17:55,480 --> 01:17:58,392
<i>RADIO: Senator, how are you going
to counter Mr Humphreys</i>

1195
01:17:58,440 --> 01:18:01,910
<i>and his backgrounding you
as far as the delegate votes go?</i>

1196
01:18:01,960 --> 01:18:04,520
<i>We're just going to have to struggle for it.</i>

1197
01:18:05,760 --> 01:18:08,752
<i>ANNOUNCER: Senator Kennedy
has been shot! Is that possible?</i>

1198
01:18:08,800 --> 01:18:10,756
<i>Is that possible?</i>

1199
01:18:10,800 --> 01:18:12,791
<i>(Shouting on radio)</i>

1200
01:18:12,840 --> 01:18:14,831
<i>(Voices fade)</i>

1201
01:18:48,520 --> 01:18:50,476
(Stones rattle)

1202
01:18:50,520 --> 01:18:52,511
Oh...

1203
01:18:52,560 --> 01:18:54,551
Charlie...

1204
01:19:03,000 --> 01:19:05,992
How you been doing? You OK?

1205
01:19:11,200 --> 01:19:14,909
<i>How can I sing the same old crap
when thousands of American kids</i>

1206
01:19:14,960 --> 01:19:17,713
<i>are getting their heads blown off
in some rice field?</i>

1207
01:19:17,760 --> 01:19:20,593
We've been lied to.
The government lies to us every day.

1208
01:19:20,640 --> 01:19:23,359
There's no end to this war.
The President lies to us.

1209
01:19:23,400 --> 01:19:25,436
The people we trust the most, they lie to us.

1210
01:19:25,480 --> 01:19:27,994
<i>- You're just all worked up.
- No, it's not that.</i>

1211
01:19:28,040 --> 01:19:31,032
Bobby Kennedy told the truth
and look what they did to him.

1212
01:19:31,080 --> 01:19:35,870
Look what he did with the time that he had.
He didn't waste his time.

1213
01:19:35,920 --> 01:19:38,275
<i>What are you doing out here?</i>

1214
01:19:38,320 --> 01:19:40,436
Sandy misses you.

1215
01:19:40,480 --> 01:19:42,471
Dodd misses you.

1216
01:19:48,320 --> 01:19:50,356
When did you meet Nina? What year?

1217
01:19:50,400 --> 01:19:54,029
Hell, I don't know. 1930-something.

1218
01:19:54,080 --> 01:19:56,799
Do you know who my father is, Charlie?

1219
01:19:56,840 --> 01:19:59,877
No, Bobby. I don't.

1220
01:20:01,160 --> 01:20:03,151
I wish I knew who he was.

1221
01:20:04,920 --> 01:20:07,832
Look, Bobby, I know...

1222
01:20:07,880 --> 01:20:10,792
I know I ain't no college boy,

1223
01:20:10,840 --> 01:20:14,799
<i>but I always kinda felt like I was your father.</i>

1224
01:20:14,840 --> 01:20:18,276
Charlie, you've been more than a father to me,
you know that.

1225
01:20:18,320 --> 01:20:20,276
I just wish I knew.

1226
01:20:20,320 --> 01:20:24,393
Stay out here much longer and Dodd's
gonna be saying the same thing about you.

1227
01:20:27,520 --> 01:20:29,511
You may not know who your father is,

1228
01:20:29,560 --> 01:20:32,597
but you got two mothers out of the deal.

1229
01:20:32,640 --> 01:20:36,997
<i>Both are of them are great.
Have you thought how hard it's been for her?</i>

1230
01:20:37,040 --> 01:20:40,953
Not to be able to tell anybody
that you're her son?

1231
01:20:41,000 --> 01:20:44,629
You wanna find yourself, get back on the stage.

1232
01:20:44,680 --> 01:20:47,911
- You are Bobby Darin.
- That's who I thought I was.

1233
01:20:47,960 --> 01:20:52,476
OK, OK, then you're Walden Robert Cassotto.

1234
01:20:52,520 --> 01:20:55,990
No, I'm not, Charlie. I'm not even him.

1235
01:20:56,040 --> 01:20:59,157
Well, maybe you're both.

1236
01:21:06,400 --> 01:21:08,960
<i>OK, Boom-Boom, let's go. We got a show to do!</i>

1237
01:21:09,000 --> 01:21:10,956
Come on! Get it on!

1238
01:21:11,000 --> 01:21:14,879
(In falsetto) # Woo-oo-ah,
yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah

1239
01:21:14,920 --> 01:21:19,471
# Ah-ah ah-ah hah,
I'll let them know, yeah!

1240
01:21:19,520 --> 01:21:23,399
# I got no mama, got no papa,
just got myself

1241
01:21:23,440 --> 01:21:26,830
# That's what I got, hoo!

1242
01:21:26,880 --> 01:21:30,316
# Come and sing the simple song of freedom

1243
01:21:30,360 --> 01:21:32,316
(Audience laugh and chat)

1244
01:21:32,360 --> 01:21:35,716
# Sing it like you've never sung before...

1245
01:21:35,760 --> 01:21:38,149
Sing Dream Lover!

1246
01:21:38,200 --> 01:21:43,274
# Let it fill the air, tell the people everywhere

1247
01:21:44,240 --> 01:21:47,994
# We the people here don't want a war

1248
01:21:49,960 --> 01:21:53,748
# Seven hundred million, are you listening?

1249
01:21:55,160 --> 01:21:59,119
<i># Most of what you read is made of lies...</i>

1250
01:21:59,160 --> 01:22:01,151
Sing Splish Splash!

1251
01:22:01,200 --> 01:22:02,918
<i># But speaking one-to-one...</i>

1252
01:22:02,960 --> 01:22:04,951
What is this, hm?

1253
01:22:05,000 --> 01:22:06,797
Is it a joke?

1254
01:22:09,600 --> 01:22:12,194
<i>STEVE: Bobby, you're turning into a total hippie!</i>

1255
01:22:12,240 --> 01:22:14,356
I don't have much time left. I'm a dying man.

1256
01:22:14,400 --> 01:22:16,834
Stop that.
I'm not gonna listen to that shit from you.

1257
01:22:16,880 --> 01:22:19,792
- It's not shit! It's the truth!
- We're all dying.

1258
01:22:19,840 --> 01:22:21,796
That's not what I'm talking about!

1259
01:22:21,840 --> 01:22:25,549
- Every day I live is a miracle!
- I know. You weren't supposed to reach 16.

1260
01:22:25,600 --> 01:22:28,353
- Don't you make fun of me, Steve!
- I'm not making fun of you!

1261
01:22:28,400 --> 01:22:32,871
<i>How am I supposed to react when you tell me
the same thing for the 2,000th time?</i>

1262
01:22:32,920 --> 01:22:35,150
<i>They booed me off the goddamn stage</i>

1263
01:22:35,200 --> 01:22:37,998
like I'd swindled them
out of their last 15 friggin' bucks!

1264
01:22:38,040 --> 01:22:41,919
They wanted to hear Dream Lover!
They're not ready for the new you!

1265
01:22:41,960 --> 01:22:44,554
They either take me as I am,
or I don't want them!

1266
01:22:44,600 --> 01:22:47,478
<i>Bobby, in seven years you've made ten films,</i>

1267
01:22:47,520 --> 01:22:51,035
won two Grammies, had seven Top 10 singles,

1268
01:22:51,080 --> 01:22:53,753
<i>got nominated for an Academy Award...</i>

1269
01:22:53,800 --> 01:22:56,189
What the hell more do you want?

1270
01:22:56,240 --> 01:22:58,708
I just gotta find myself, that's all.

1271
01:22:59,800 --> 01:23:02,872
Everybody else seems to know who you are.

1272
01:23:02,920 --> 01:23:05,354
But you keep looking.

1273
01:23:06,160 --> 01:23:08,151
When you find yourself, give me a call.

1274
01:23:08,200 --> 01:23:10,236
Then we'll see where we are.

1275
01:23:13,560 --> 01:23:15,551
Steve...

1276
01:23:17,080 --> 01:23:19,514
You don't really think I'm crazy?

1277
01:23:27,240 --> 01:23:29,708
My watch is slowing down.

1278
01:23:33,280 --> 01:23:35,271
Better get this fixed.

1279
01:23:43,360 --> 01:23:45,351
<i>What does "your time's up" mean?</i>

1280
01:23:45,400 --> 01:23:47,789
What are you talking about?

1281
01:23:48,840 --> 01:23:52,833
My friend Gregory said that my time's up.

1282
01:23:52,880 --> 01:23:56,589
Your time's up! Bullshit. Here.

1283
01:23:56,640 --> 01:23:59,677
You wear that when you get older. Hm?

1284
01:24:03,360 --> 01:24:05,669
I'm gonna get older?

1285
01:24:05,720 --> 01:24:07,676
Well, sure, you are.

1286
01:24:07,720 --> 01:24:11,998
But you gotta believe it.
You always gotta believe it, Bobby.

1287
01:24:12,040 --> 01:24:15,874
<i>As long as you really believe it, it's true.</i>

1288
01:24:19,120 --> 01:24:21,111
(Ticking)

1289
01:24:33,160 --> 01:24:35,116
Hey.

1290
01:24:35,160 --> 01:24:37,151
You're back.

1291
01:24:38,640 --> 01:24:40,631
How do you feel?

1292
01:24:44,680 --> 01:24:47,478
Like somebody's had their hands in my chest.

1293
01:24:47,520 --> 01:24:49,511
Yeah. They said it went well.

1294
01:24:49,560 --> 01:24:51,869
They replaced both valves.

1295
01:24:55,240 --> 01:24:57,231
It won't last, Charlie.

1296
01:24:59,000 --> 01:25:01,798
Ah, that's just the medication talking.

1297
01:25:01,840 --> 01:25:04,195
<i>- You need to eat.
- I need to eat?</i>

1298
01:25:04,240 --> 01:25:06,231
Yeah.

1299
01:25:07,520 --> 01:25:09,476
You can't have this yet,

1300
01:25:09,520 --> 01:25:12,353
but I want you to have something
to look forward to.

1301
01:25:12,400 --> 01:25:14,356
- Well, what is it?
- Manicotti.

1302
01:25:14,400 --> 01:25:16,755
We got good manicotti.

1303
01:25:16,800 --> 01:25:21,351
And Nina sent her spaghetti
all the way from New York.

1304
01:25:21,400 --> 01:25:25,678
Nina's spaghetti?
What are you trying to do, kill me, Charlie?

1305
01:25:25,720 --> 01:25:27,995
She misses you, Bobby.

1306
01:25:31,320 --> 01:25:35,632
I'll just call her and Sandy
and tell everybody that you're OK. OK?

1307
01:25:43,000 --> 01:25:46,276
Nine hours on the operating table,
and he keeps on ticking!

1308
01:25:46,320 --> 01:25:48,515
Oh, yeah. I just have one thing to say.

1309
01:25:48,560 --> 01:25:51,677
I bet old Dr Andretti, old dead Dr Andretti,

1310
01:25:51,720 --> 01:25:55,429
would sure be surprised
to see I made it to my 36th birthday!

1311
01:26:01,440 --> 01:26:03,476
Don't steal that! It's not yours!

1312
01:26:08,960 --> 01:26:11,030
Ha-Happy birthday.

1313
01:26:11,080 --> 01:26:14,311
Thank you, Nina. You look great.
That's a nice outfit.

1314
01:26:14,360 --> 01:26:17,318
You like it?
Cos I got it special for your birthday.

1315
01:26:17,360 --> 01:26:21,638
I wanted you to know that your mother
can be a classy lady.

1316
01:26:22,680 --> 01:26:24,398
What, Bobby?

1317
01:26:25,520 --> 01:26:27,112
What, Bobby?

1318
01:26:28,080 --> 01:26:30,640
It's OK, Nina. I think I know why you told me.

1319
01:26:30,680 --> 01:26:32,557
<i>Excuse me for a minute.</i>

1320
01:26:35,400 --> 01:26:37,356
- Hi.
- Don't he look great?

1321
01:26:37,400 --> 01:26:39,470
- Don't he look great?
- He looks great.

1322
01:26:39,520 --> 01:26:42,637
He looks like a million bucks.
He's gonna live to be 100.

1323
01:26:42,680 --> 01:26:45,752
Hey. I've been looking for you all day.

1324
01:26:45,800 --> 01:26:49,076
- No, you haven't, you liar.
- I have. I have.

1325
01:26:49,120 --> 01:26:52,157
- You look so good.
- Oh, I feel good.

1326
01:26:52,200 --> 01:26:54,156
I feel great, physically.

1327
01:26:54,200 --> 01:26:59,399
In so much as I can actually breathe easy
for the first time since I can remember.

1328
01:27:00,760 --> 01:27:02,751
<i>Dodd misses you being home.</i>

1329
01:27:05,000 --> 01:27:06,991
I miss you.

1330
01:27:09,680 --> 01:27:11,716
I'm proud of you, baby.

1331
01:27:11,760 --> 01:27:14,479
- I'm really trying, Bobby.
- I know you are.

1332
01:27:14,520 --> 01:27:17,432
That's not why you left. There's more than that.

1333
01:27:18,440 --> 01:27:22,718
I'm not what you want me to be.
I'm not an intellectual, I'm not as smart as you.

1334
01:27:22,760 --> 01:27:24,876
You're smart enough for ten of me.

1335
01:27:26,280 --> 01:27:29,078
And look what we did together.

1336
01:27:31,840 --> 01:27:34,559
- You gonna sing again?
- Oh, I'd love to.

1337
01:27:34,600 --> 01:27:38,718
I'm just not sure I can get used to the idea
of booing as a nightly ritual.

1338
01:27:38,760 --> 01:27:41,752
Oh, you can't blame them.
They don't understand.

1339
01:27:41,800 --> 01:27:43,518
You were always ahead of your time.

1340
01:27:44,560 --> 01:27:47,757
They're so shallow.
People hear what they see, anyway.

1341
01:27:49,480 --> 01:27:51,914
Yeah. I know, the...

1342
01:27:52,840 --> 01:27:55,991
- What did you just say?
- That you can't blame them...

1343
01:27:56,040 --> 01:27:59,555
No, no, no. About people hearing what?

1344
01:27:59,600 --> 01:28:01,556
<i>Boom-Boom! Boom-Boom! Boom-Boom!</i>

1345
01:28:01,600 --> 01:28:04,068
Boom-Boom, Boom-Boom, Boom-Boom.

1346
01:28:06,320 --> 01:28:08,311
Book me back in Vegas.

1347
01:28:10,240 --> 01:28:12,196
You don't wanna go back to Vegas.

1348
01:28:12,240 --> 01:28:15,994
Oh, yes, I do. I wanna go back to Vegas,
and I wanna go back on stage.

1349
01:28:16,040 --> 01:28:18,190
<i>Don't tell me you found yourself.</i>

1350
01:28:18,240 --> 01:28:20,834
- He's going back to Vegas?
- First I've heard.

1351
01:28:20,880 --> 01:28:23,110
I'm a nightclub animal, Boom-Boom,
and I love it.

1352
01:28:23,160 --> 01:28:25,958
Frankly, I think I do it better
than anybody else in the world.

1353
01:28:26,000 --> 01:28:29,549
You're also modest,
but I don't want you going back there.

1354
01:28:29,600 --> 01:28:31,556
<i>It's gonna work this time.</i>

1355
01:28:31,600 --> 01:28:34,717
I can be what I want,
I can say what I want, I can sing what I want.

1356
01:28:34,760 --> 01:28:37,991
Sandy just said it. She just said it beautifully.

1357
01:28:38,040 --> 01:28:38,950
What?

1358
01:28:40,000 --> 01:28:41,877
People hear what they see.

1359
01:28:53,400 --> 01:28:59,032
It's funny. You weren't a girl
a guy like me was supposed to get.

1360
01:28:59,080 --> 01:29:01,389
I mean, there I was, a singer from the Bronx,

1361
01:29:01,440 --> 01:29:04,159
and there you were, a movie star.

1362
01:29:11,800 --> 01:29:14,109
Bobby, what's gonna happen to me?

1363
01:29:16,360 --> 01:29:21,070
No matter what happens, baby,
you'll always be Sandra Dee.

1364
01:29:45,720 --> 01:29:48,996
- Why can't I open it?
- Because it's not like the gifts you're used to.

1365
01:29:49,040 --> 01:29:53,238
This one is very, very special
and nobody can know you have it.

1366
01:29:53,280 --> 01:29:55,236
What's in it?

1367
01:29:55,280 --> 01:29:59,671
$2 million hard cash,
but unfortunately it's Confederate money, so...

1368
01:29:59,720 --> 01:30:01,995
- Dad!
- No.

1369
01:30:02,040 --> 01:30:04,679
It's just some things I want you to have.

1370
01:30:04,720 --> 01:30:07,393
So nobody can know I have it? Not even Mom?

1371
01:30:07,440 --> 01:30:10,671
Not Mom, not Charlie,
not Aunt Nina, or Grandma.

1372
01:30:10,720 --> 01:30:13,154
Nobody but you and me. It's a secret.

1373
01:30:13,200 --> 01:30:15,555
When can I open it?

1374
01:30:17,960 --> 01:30:19,951
When I'm gone.

1375
01:30:22,080 --> 01:30:24,036
I don't want you to die, Dad.

1376
01:30:24,080 --> 01:30:27,390
Well, you know, Moose,
I'm no different than anybody else.

1377
01:30:27,440 --> 01:30:30,432
My time might just come a little sooner,
that's all.

1378
01:30:30,480 --> 01:30:33,199
- What about me?
- What about you?

1379
01:30:33,240 --> 01:30:35,231
You're gonna be just fine...

1380
01:30:36,080 --> 01:30:38,833
...if you're the man I think you are.

1381
01:30:38,880 --> 01:30:43,874
You know, I had to fight my way out of the Bronx
to make something of myself.

1382
01:30:43,920 --> 01:30:48,311
But not nearly as hard as you're gonna
have to fight to get out of Beverly Hills.

1383
01:31:03,200 --> 01:31:04,713
How you doing in there?

1384
01:31:05,560 --> 01:31:09,314
<i>- Trying to find a heartbeat.
- That's not funny.</i>

1385
01:31:09,360 --> 01:31:12,557
<i>- Are my tux and toupee laid out?
- Yeah.</i>

1386
01:31:12,600 --> 01:31:15,672
You got nothing to worry about.

1387
01:31:17,280 --> 01:31:19,236
You don't look so good.

1388
01:31:20,440 --> 01:31:23,591
To tell you the truth, Charlie, I don't feel so hot.

1389
01:31:23,640 --> 01:31:27,428
I gotta go under the knife again,
that's why we're taking off early.

1390
01:31:27,480 --> 01:31:30,119
I got blood poisoning. It's catching up.

1391
01:31:30,160 --> 01:31:33,789
Look, we don't have to do this.
We can call it off.

1392
01:31:33,840 --> 01:31:36,559
Charlie, I gotta get ready now.

1393
01:31:39,680 --> 01:31:42,638
I gotta go make sure Nina's at a good table.

1394
01:31:46,000 --> 01:31:48,958
Charlie, I wouldn't have gone this far
without you.

1395
01:31:49,000 --> 01:31:52,595
Kid, you were a runaway train.

1396
01:31:52,640 --> 01:31:55,313
- Just get through tonight.
- Yeah.

1397
01:31:55,360 --> 01:31:57,590
Always leave 'em wanting more, Charlie.

1398
01:32:18,960 --> 01:32:20,916
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

1399
01:32:20,960 --> 01:32:25,192
<i>would you please welcome back
to the Flamingo stage an old friend,</i>

1400
01:32:25,240 --> 01:32:27,834
<i>one of this country's greatest entertainers.</i>

1401
01:32:27,880 --> 01:32:32,192
<i>Academy Award nominee,
two-time Grammy winner...</i>

1402
01:32:33,400 --> 01:32:36,597
<i>Sing Dream Lover! (Laughs)</i>

1403
01:32:37,720 --> 01:32:41,395
<i>The Flamingo Hotel is proud to present...</i>

1404
01:32:43,360 --> 01:32:46,955
<i>...the legendary Bobby Darin!</i>

1405
01:32:48,800 --> 01:32:50,791
(Applause)

1406
01:32:50,840 --> 01:32:52,831
